      • create

        @Nullable
Validator<?> create(java.lang.reflect.Type type,
                              java.util.Set<? extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> annotations,
                              Inspector inspector)
        Attempts to create an adapter for type annotated with annotations. This returns the adapter if one was created, or null if this factory isn't capable of creating such an adapter.

        Implementations may use to Inspector.validator(java.lang.reflect.Type) to compose adapters of other types, or Inspector.nextValidator(io.sweers.inspector.Validator.Factory, java.lang.reflect.Type, java.util.Set<? extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation>) to delegate to the underlying adapter of the same type.
